OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: THE STATION IS LOCATED ON THE LAS TRAMPAS RIDGE CA 7.5 MINUTE SERIES (TOPOGRAPHIC) QUADRANGLE.  THE SPRING IS LOCATED APPROXIMATELY 1000 FEET TO THE SOUTHWEST OF EUGENE O'NEIL NATIONAL HISTORIC SITE AND IS OWNED BY THE NATIONAL PARK SERVICE.  THE DATA ARE FROM THE CENTRAL FILES ARCHIVE AT THE NATIONAL PARK SERVICE WATER RESOURCES DIVISION IN FORT COLLINS COLORADO.  THE SPRING APPEARS TO HAVE BEEN DEVELOPED YEARS AGO BY A FRENCH DRAIN SYSTEM AND HAS A SERIES OF PIPES WHICH DELIVER WATER BY FREE FALL INTO A CIRCULAR HOLDING WELL; WHERE IT IS THEN PIPED TO THREE REDWOOD STORAGE TANKS.  DATA WERE PROCESSED AND UPLOADED TO STORET BY MELANIE SCHNIER AT NPSWRD; 1201 OAK RIDGE DRIVE SUITE 250; FORT COLLINS CO 80525; TEL 9702253516.***     Legacy STORET Station Type: /TYPA/AMBNT/SPRING

THIS STATION IS ONE OF A GROUP OF STATIONS MONITORED AT LOBOS CREEK BY THE CITY AND COUNTY OF SAN FRANCISCO DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC WORKS (CCSF) AS A PRELIMINARY INVESTIGATION TO IDENTIFY THE SOURCE OF HIGH COLIFORM COUNTS APPEARING DOWNSTREAM AT CCSF SHORELINE STATIONS.
